S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Water that is suitable for human consumption.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Milk
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A white fluid secreted by female mammals as food for their young.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bauxite
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mineral from which aluminum is obtained.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coke
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A solid substance obtained after gas and tar have been extracted from coal, used as a fuel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Iron Ingots
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An oblong lump of cast iron metal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Salt
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Sodium chloride obtained from mines or by the evaporation of sea water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sand
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Loose material consisting of small but easily distinguishable, separate grains, between 0.0625 and 2.000 millimetres in diameter.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Timber
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Wood prepared for use in building or carpentry.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sawdust/Wood Chips
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Powdery fragments of wood made in sawing timber or coarse chips produced for use in manufacturing pressed board.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Scrap Metal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Discarded metal suitable for being reprocessed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Liquefied Natural Gas
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Natural gas that has been liquefied for ease of transport by cooling the gas to -162 Celsius.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Liquefied Petroleum Gas
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A compressed gas consisting of flammable light hydrocarbons and derived from petroleum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wine
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The fermented juice of grapes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cement
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A substance made of powdered lime and clay, mixed with water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Grain
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A small hard seed, especially that of any cereal plant such as wheat, rice, corn, rye etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Electricity
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Electric charge or current.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ice
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The solid form of water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Clay
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (Particles of less than 0.002mm); stiff, sticky earth that becomes hard when baked.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Offshore Platform
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of an offshore raised structure.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Oil Rig
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A temporary mobile structure, either fixed or floating, used in the exploration stages of oil and gas fields.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Production Platform
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A term used to indicate a permanent offshore structure equipped to control the flow of oil or gas. It does not include entirely submarine structures.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Observation/Research Platform
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A platform from which one's surroundings or events can be observed, noted or recorded such as for scientific study.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Articulated Loading Platform
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A metal lattice tower, buoyant at one end and attached at the other by a universal joint to a concrete filled base on the sea bed. The platform may be fitted with a helicopter platform, emergency accommodation and hawser/hose retrieval.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Single Anchor Leg Mooring
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rigid frame or tube with a buoyancy device at its upper end , secured at its lower end to a universal joint on a large steel or concrete base resting on the sea bed, and at its upper end to a mooring buoy by a chain or wire.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mooring Tower
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A platform secured to the sea bed and surmounted by a turntable to which ships moor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Artificial Island
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A man-made structure usually built for the exploration or exploitation of marine resources, marine scientific research, tidal observations, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Floating Production, Storage and Off-Loading Vessel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An offshore oil/gas facility consisting of a moored tanker/barge by which the product is extracted, stored and exported.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Accommodation Platform
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A platform used primarily for eating, sleeping and recreation purposes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Navigation, Communication and Control Buoy
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A floating structure with control room, power and storage facilities, attached to the sea bed by a flexible pipeline and cables.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Floating Oil Tank
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A floating structure, anchored to the seabed, for storing oil.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Width
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A measurement of the shorter of two linear axis.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Length
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A measurement of the longer of two linear axis.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Cardinal Mark
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The four quadrants (north, east, south and west) are bounded by the true bearings NW-NE, NE-SE, SE-SW and SW-NW taken from the point of interest. A cardinal mark is named after the quadrant in which it is placed. The name of the cardinal mark indicates that it should be passed to the named side of the mark.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Cardinal marks are used in conjunction with the compass to indicate where a mariner will find safe navigable water.Cardinal marks do not have a distinctive shape but are normally pillar or spar. They are always painted in yellow and black horizontal bands and their distinctive double cone top-marks are always black. (Note that such top-marks are encoded as separate TOPMAR objects). Cardinal marks may also have a special system of flashing white lights and if such lights are fitted they are encoded as separate LIGHTS objects.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: North Cardinal Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Quadrant bounded by the true bearing NW-NE taken from the point of interest; it should be passed to the north side of the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: East Cardinal Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Quadrant bounded by the true bearing NE-SE taken from the point of interest. It should be passed to the east side of the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: South Cardinal Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Quadrant bounded by the true bearing SE-SW taken from the point of interest; it should be passed to the south side of the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: West Cardinal Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Quadrant bounded by the true bearing SW-NW taken from the point of interest; it should be passed to the west side of the mark.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Type of Light
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Type of light equipment.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: For example bulb type (250mm, 300mm, 400mm), LED type (integral type, 200, 200HI, 250, 300, 350).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: NMEAString
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: NMEA string captured from the positioning device.(proposed by CCG)

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Light Characteristic
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The distinct character, such as fixed, flashing, or occulting, which is given to each light to avoid confusion with neighbouring ones.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fixed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A signal light that shows continuously, in any given direction, with constant luminous intensity and colour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which the total duration of light in a period is clearly shorter than the total duration of darkness and all the appearances of light are of equal duration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Long-Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A single-flashing light in which a single flash of not less than two seconds duration is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Quick-Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which flashes are repeated at a rate of not less than 50 flashes per minutes but less than 80 flashes per minutes. It may be: - Continuous quick-flashing: A quick-flashing light in which a flash is regularly repeated. - Group quick-flashing: A quick-flashing light in which a group of two or more flashes, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Very Quick-Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which flashes are repeated at a rate of not less than 80 flashes per minute but less than 160 flashes per minute. It may be:- Continuous very quick-flashing: A very quick-flashing light in which a flash is regularly repeated.- Group very quick-flashing: A very quick-flashing light in which a group of two or more flashes, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Continuous Ultra Quick-Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which flashes are regularly repeated at a rate of not less than 160 flashes per minute.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Isophased
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light with all durations of light and darkness equal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Occulting
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which the total duration of light in a period is clearly longer than the total duration of darkness and all the eclipses are of equal duration. It may be: - Single-occulting: An occulting light in which an eclipse is regularly repeated. - Group-occulting: An occulting light in which a group of two or more eclipses, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated. - Composite group-occulting: An occulting light in which a sequence of groups of one or more eclipses, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated, and the groups comprise different numbers of eclipses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Morse
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which appearances of light of two clearly different durations are grouped to represent a character or characters in the Morse code.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fixed and Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a fixed light is combined with a flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flash and Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a flashing light is combined with a long-flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Occulting and Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which an occulting light is combined with a flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fixed and Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a fixed light is combined with a long-flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Occulting Alternating
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An alternating light in which the total duration of light in each period is clearly longer than the total duration of darkness and in which the intervals of darkness (occultations) are all of equal duration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Long-Flash Alternating
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An alternating single-flashing light in which an appearance of light of not less than two seconds duration is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flash Alternating
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An alternating rhythmic light in which the total duration of light in a period is clearly shorter than the total duration of darkness and all the appearances of light are of equal duration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Group Alternating
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Occulting light in which the occultations are combined in groups, each group including the same number of occultations, and in which the groups are repeated at regular intervals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Quick-Flash Plus Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a group of quick flashes is followed by one or more long flashes in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Very Quick-Flash Plus Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a group of very quick flashes is followed by one or more long flashes in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ultra Quick-Flash Plus Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a group of ultra quick flashes is followed by one or more long flashes in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Alternating
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A signal light that shows, in any given direction, two or more colours in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Group-occulting light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An occulting light in which a group of two or more eclipses, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Composite group-occulting light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An occulting light in which a sequence of groups of one or more eclipses, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated, and the groups comprise different numbers of eclipses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Group flashing light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A flashing light in which a group of flashes, specified in number, is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Composite group-flashing light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light similar to a group-flashing light except that successive groups in a period have different numbers of flashes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Group quick light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A quick-flashing light in which a group of two or more flashes, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Group very quick light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A very quick-flashing light in which a group of two or more flashes, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category Of Synthetic AIS Aid To Navigation
Category Of Physical AIS Aid To Navigation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A classification of AIS AtoNs that correspond to an actual, physical Aid to Navigation at a real-world location.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Physical AIS Type 1
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Simple transmission of static, pre-programmed information.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Physical AIS Type 2
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Transmission of dynamic, real-time updated information via connected sensors.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Physical AIS Type 3
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Full two-way communication: transmission + remote control / configuration.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Virtual AIS Aid to Navigation Type
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A purpose of a virtual AIS Aid to Navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: North Cardinal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that it should be passed to the north side of the aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: East Cardinal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that it should be passed to the east side of the aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: South Cardinal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that it should be passed to the south side of the aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: West Cardinal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that it should be passed to the west side of the aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Port Lateral
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates the port boundary of a navigational channel or suggested route when proceeding in the conventional direction of buoyage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Starboard Lateral
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates the starboard boundary of a navigational channel or suggested route when proceeding in the conventional direction of buoyage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Preferred Channel to Port
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: At a point where a channel divides, when proceeding in the conventional direction of buoyage, the preferred channel (or primary route) is indicated by a modified port-hand lateral mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Preferred Channel to Starboard
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: At a point where a channel divides, when proceeding in the conventional direction of buoyage, the preferred channel (or primary route) is indicated by a modified starboard-hand lateral mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Isolated Danger
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used alone to indicate a dangerous reef or shoal. The mark may be passed on either hand.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Safe Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that there is navigable water around the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Special Purpose
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A special purpose aid is primarily used to indicate an area or feature, the nature of which is apparent from reference to a chart, Sailing Directions or Notice to Mariners

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: New Danger Marking
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the existence of a recently identified new danger, such as a wreck.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: MMSI Code
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The Maritime Mobile Service Identity (MMSI) Code is formed of a series of nine digits which are transmitted over the radio path in order to uniquely identify ship stations, ship earth stations,coast stations, coast earth stations, and group calls. These identities are formed in such a way that the identity or part thereof can be used by telephone and telex subscribers connected to the general telecommunications network principally to call ships automatically.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Radar Transponder Beacon
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of radar transponder beacon based on functionality.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ramark, Radar Beacon Transmitting Continuously
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A radar marker beacon which continuously transmits a signal appearing as a radial line on a radar screen, the line indicating the direction of the beacon. Ramarks are intended primarily for marine use. The name 'ramark' is derived from the words radar marker.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Racon, Radar Transponder Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A radar beacon which returns a coded signal which provides identification of the beacon, as well as range and bearing. The range and bearing are indicated by the location of the first character received on the radar screen. The name 'racon' is derived from the words radar beacon.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Leading Racon/Radar Transponder Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A radar beacon that may be used (in conjunction with at least one other radar beacon) to indicate a leading line.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Topmark/Daymark Shape
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The shape a topmark or daymark exhibits.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cone (Point Up)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Is where the vertex points up. A cone is a solid figure generated by straight lines drawn from a fixed point (the vertex) to a circle in a plane not containing the vertex. Cones are commonly used as International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities - IALA topmarks, lateral.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cone (Point Down)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Is where the vertex points down. A cone is a solid figure generated by straight lines drawn from a fixed point (the vertex) to a circle in a plane not containing the vertex. Cones are commonly used as International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities - IALA topmarks, lateral.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sphere
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A curved surface all points of which are equidistant from a fixed point within, called the centre.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: 2 Spheres
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Two spheres, one above the other. Two black spheres are commonly used as an International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities - IALA topmark (isolated danger).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cylinder
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A solid geometrical figure generated by straight lines fixed in direction and describing with one of point a closed curve, especially a circle (in which case the figure is circular cylinder, it's ends being parallel circles). Cylinders are commonly used as International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities - IALA topmarks lateral.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Board
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Usually of rectangular shape, made from timber or metal and used to provide a contrast with the natural background of a daymark. The actual daymark is often painted on to this board.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: X-Shaped
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Having a shape or a cross-section like the capital letter X. An x-shape as an International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities - IALA topmark should be 3 dimensional in shape. It is made of at least three crossed bars.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Upright Cross
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A cross with one vertical member and one horizontal member; that is, similar in shape to the character '+'.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cube (Point Up)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A cube standing on one of its vertexes. A cube is a solid contained by six equal squares, a regular hexahedron.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: 2 Cones (Point to Point)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 2 cones, one above the other, with their vertices together in the centre.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: 2 Cones (Base to Base)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 2 cones, one above the other, with their bases together in the centre and their vertices pointing up and down.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rhombus
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A plane figure having four equal sides and equal opposite angles (two acute and two obtuse); an oblique equilateral parallelogram.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: 2 Cones (Points Upward)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 2 cones, one above the other, with their vertices pointing up.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: 2 Cones (Points Downward)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: 2 cones, one above the other, with their vertices pointing down.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Besom (Point Up)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Besom: A bundle of rods or twigs. Perch: A staff placed on top of a buoy, rock or shoal as a mark for navigation. A besom, point up is where the thicker (untied) end of the besom is at the bottom.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Besom (Point Down)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Besom: A bundle of rods or twigs. Perch: A staff placed on top of a buoy, rock or shoal as a mark for navigation. A besom, point down is where the thinner (tied) end of the besom is at the bottom.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flag
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A flag mounted on a short pole.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sphere Over a Rhombus
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A sphere located above a rhombus.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Square
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A plane figure with four right angles and four equal straight sides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rectangle (Horizontal)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Where the two longer opposite sides are standing horizontally. A rectangle is a plane figure with four right angles and four straight sides, opposite sides being parallel and equal in length.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rectangle (Vertical)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Where the two longer opposite sides are standing vertically. A rectangle is a plane figure with four right angles and four straight sides, opposite sides being parallel and equal in length.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Trapezium (Up)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A quadrilateral having one pair of opposite sides parallel, and which stands on its longer parallel side.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Trapezium (Down)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A quadrilateral having one pair of opposite sides parallel, and which stands on its shorter parallel side.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Triangle (Point Up)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A figure having three angles and three sides, and which has a vertex at the top.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Triangle (Point Down)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A figure having three angles and three sides, and which has a side at the top.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Circle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A perfectly round plane figure whose circumference is everywhere equidistant from its centre.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Two Upright Crosses (One Over the Other)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Two upright crosses, generally vertically disposed one above the other.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: T-Shape
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Having a shape like the capital letter T.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Triangle Pointing Up Over a Circle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A triangle, vertex uppermost, located above a circle.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Upright Cross Over a Circle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An upright cross located above a circle.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rhombus Over a Circle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhombus located above a circle.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Circle Over a Triangle Pointing Up
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A circle located over a triangle, vertex uppermost.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Other Shape (See Shape Information)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An uncommon and/or non-standardized shape as textually described using an associated attribute.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Tubular
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Having the form of or consisting of a tube.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Orientation Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The angular distance measured from true north to the major axis of the feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Special Purpose Mark
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of an aid to navigation which signifies some special purpose.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: A mark may be a beacon, a buoy, a signpost or may take another form.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Firing Danger Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate a firing danger area, usually at sea.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Target Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any object toward which something is directed. The distinctive marking or instrumentation of a ground point to aid its identification on a photograph.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Marker Ship Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark marking the position of a ship which is used as a target during some military exercise.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Degaussing Range Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate a degaussing range.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Barge Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark of relevance to barges.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cable Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the position of submarine cables or the point at which they run on to the land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spoil Ground Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the limit of a spoil ground.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Outfall Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the position of an outfall or the point at which it leaves the land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ODAS
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Ocean Data Acquisition System.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Recording Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to record data for scientific purposes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Seaplane Anchorage Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate a seaplane anchorage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Recreation Zone Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate a recreation zone.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Private Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A privately maintained mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mooring Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating a mooring or moorings.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: LANBY
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A large buoy designed to take the place of a lightship where construction of an offshore light station is not feasible.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Leading Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Aids to navigation or other indicators so located as to indicate the path to be followed. Leading marks identify a leading line when they are in transit.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Measured Distance Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark forming part of a transit indicating one end of a measured distance.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Notice Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A notice board or sign indicating information to the mariner.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: TSS Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating a Traffic Separation Scheme.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Anchoring Prohibited Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating an anchoring prohibited area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Berthing Prohibited Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that berthing is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Overtaking Prohibited Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that overtaking is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Two-Way Traffic Prohibited Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating a one-way route.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Reduced Wake Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that vessels must not generate excessive wake.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Speed Limit Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that a speed limit applies.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stop Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the place where the bow of a ship must stop when traffic lights show red.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: General Warning Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that special caution must be exercised in the vicinity of the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sound Ship's Siren Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that a ship should sound its siren or horn.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Restricted Vertical Clearance Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the minimum vertical space available for passage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Maximum Vessel's Draught Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the maximum draught of vessel permitted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Restricted Horizontal Clearance Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the minimum horizontal space available for passage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Strong Current Warning Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark warning of strong currents.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Berthing Permitted Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that berthing is allowed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Overhead Power Cable Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating an overhead power cable.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Channel Edge Gradient Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the gradient of the slope of a dredge channel edge.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Telephone Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the presence of a telephone.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ferry Crossing Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that a ferry route crosses the ship route; often used with a 'sound ship's siren' mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pipeline Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the position of submarine pipelines or the point at which they run on to the land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Anchorage Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating an anchorage area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Clearing Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate a clearing line.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Control Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the location at which a restriction or requirement exists.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Diving Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that diving may take place in the vicinity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Refuge Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark providing or indicating a place of safety.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Foul Ground Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating a foul ground.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Yachting Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark installed for use by yachtsmen.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Heliport Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating an area where helicopters may land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: GNSS Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating a location at which a GNSS position has been accurately determined.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Seaplane Landing Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating an area where sea-planes land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Entry Prohibited Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that entry is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Work in Progress Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating that work (generally construction) is in progress.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mark With Unknown Purpose
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark whose detailed characteristics are unknown.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wellhead Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating a borehole that produces or is capable of producing oil or natural gas.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Channel Separation Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the point at which a channel divides separately into two channels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Marine Farm Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the existence of a fish, mussel, oyster or pearl farm/culture.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Artificial Reef Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating the existence or the extent of an artificial reef.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ice Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark, used year round, that may be submerged when ice passes through the area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nature Reserve Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to define the boundary of a nature reserve.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fish Aggregating Device
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A fish aggregating (or aggregation) device (FAD) is a man-made object used to attract ocean going pelagic fish such as marlin, tuna and mahi-mahi (dolphin fish). They usually consist of buoys or floats tethered to the ocean floor with concrete blocks.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wreck Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the existence of a wreck.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Customs Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the existence of a customs checkpoint.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Causeway Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the existence of a causeway.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wave Recorder
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A surface following buoy used to measure wave activity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Jetski Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark indicating a jetski prohibited area.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Estimated Range of Transmission
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The estimated range of a non-optical electromagnetic transmission.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The estimated range (distance) assumes 'in vacuo' transmission and a standard antenna height of 5 metres. Thus it gives a hint to the mariner whether they are likely to receive transmission at a certain distance from an object.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Radio Station
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of radio services offered by a radio station.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: A radiobeacon is a radio transmitter which emits a distinctive or characteristic signal on which a bearing may be taken.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Circular (Non-Directional) Marine or Aero-Marine Radiobeacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A radio station which need not necessarily be manned, the emissions of which, radiated around the horizon, enable its bearing to be determined by means of the radio direction finder of a ship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Directional Radiobeacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A special type of radiobeacon station the emissions of which are intended to provide a definite track for guidance.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rotating Pattern Radiobeacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A special type of radiobeacon station emitting a beam of waves to which a uniform turning movement is given, the bearing of the station being determined by means of an ordinary listening receiver and a stop watch. Also referred to as a rotating loop radiobeacon.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Consol Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A type of long range position fixing beacon.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Radio Direction-Finding Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A radio station intended to determine only the direction of other stations by means of transmission from the latter.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coast Radio Station Providing QTG Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A radio station which is prepared to provide QTG service; that is to say, to transmit upon request from a ship a radio signal, the bearing of which can be taken by that ship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Aeronautical Radiobeacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A radio beacon designed for aeronautical use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Decca
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The Decca Navigator System is a high accuracy, short to medium range radio navigational aid intended for coastal and landfall navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Loran C
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A low frequency electronic position fixing system using pulsed transmissions at 100 Khz.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Differential GNSS
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A radiobeacon transmitting DGPS correction signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Toran
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An electronic position fixing system used mainly by aircraft.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Omega
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A long-range radio navigational aid which operates within the VLF frequency band. The system comprises eight land based stations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Syledis
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A ranging position fixing system operating at 420-450 MHz over a range of up to 400 Km.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Chaika
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Chaika is a low frequency electronic position fixing system using pulsed transmissions at 100 Khz.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Radio Telephone Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The equipment needed at one station to carry on two way voice communication by radio waves only.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: AIS Base Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An onshore AIS unit that monitors traffic in the waterways.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Type of Environmental Observation Equipment
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Type of sensor used to observe the environment. For example Anemometer, fog monitor, etc.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Value of Maximum Range
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The extreme distance at which an feature can be seen or a signal detected.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Does not apply to lights where the 'value of nominal range' should be used.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal Period
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The time occupied by an entire cycle of intervals of light and eclipse.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal Output
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Strength of signal output.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal Group
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The number of signals, the combination of signals or the morse character(s) within one period of full sequence.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal Frequency
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The frequency of a signal.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Flare Bearing
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The bearing about which the light flare symbol is rotated to be displayed in ECDIS.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Fog Signal
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of the various means of generating the fog signal.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The classification 'horn' is the generic term for fog signals 'nautophone', 'reed' and 'tyfon'.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Explosive
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A signal produced by the firing of explosive charges.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Diaphone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A diaphone uses compressed air and generally emits a powerful low-pitched sound, which often concludes with a brief sound of suddenly lowered pitch, termed the 'grunt'.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Siren
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A type of fog signal apparatus which produces sound by virtue of the passage of air through slots or holes in a revolving disk.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nautophone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A horn having a diaphragm oscillated by electricity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Reed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: [1] A reed uses compressed air and emits a weak, high pitched sound. [2] Any of various water or marsh plants with a firm stem. (Concise Oxford English Dictionary)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Tyfon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A diaphragm horn which operates under the influence of compressed air or steam.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bell
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A ringing sound with a short range.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Whistle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A distinctive sound made by a jet of air passing through an orifice. The apparatus may be operated automatically, by hand or by air being forced up a tube by waves acting on a buoy.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Gong
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A sound produced by vibration of a disc when struck.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Horn
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A horn uses compressed air or electricity to vibrate a diaphragm and exists in a variety of types which differ greatly in their sound and power.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Value of Nominal Range
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The luminous range of a light in a homogenous atmosphere in which the meteorological visibility is 10 sea miles.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Major Light
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement expressing if a light is considered to be a major light in terms of ECDIS display in a particular area.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Major light is only intended to provide an indication to the ECDIS that the light is considered to be an important light in terms of its display. As such this is a cartographic attribute to aid the compiler in determining the most appropriate display for a light; it is not intended to be used as a formal classification method for lights.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Light Visibility
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The specific visibility of a light, with respect to the light's intensity and ease of recognition.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: High Intensity
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Non-marine lights with a higher power than marine lights and visible from well off shore (often 'Aero' lights).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Low Intensity
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Non-marine lights with lower power than marine lights.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Faint
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A decrease in the apparent intensity of a light which may occur in the case of partial obstructions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Intensified
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light in a sector is intensified (that is, has longer range than other sectors).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unintensified
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light in a sector is unintensified (that is, has shorter range than other sectors).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Visibility Deliberately Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light sector is deliberately reduced in intensity, for example to reduce its effect on a built-up area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Obscured
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Said of the arc of a light sector designated by its limiting bearings in which the light is not visible from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Partially Obscured
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: This value specifies that parts of the sector are obscured.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Visible in Line of Range
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Lights that must in line to be visible.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal Generation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The mechanism used to generate a fog or light signal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Automatically
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Signal generation is initiated by a self regulating mechanism such as a timer or light sensor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: By Wave Action
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The signal is generated by the motion of the sea surface such as a bell in a buoy.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: By Hand
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The signal is generated by a manually operated mechanism such as a hand cranked siren.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: By Wind
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The signal is generated by the motion of air such as a wind driven whistle.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Radio Activated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Activated by radio signal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Call Activated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Activated by making a call to a manned station.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Exhibition Condition of Light
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The outward display of the light.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Light Shown Without Change of Character
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light shown throughout the 24 hours without change of character.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Daytime Light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light which is only exhibited by day.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fog Light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light which is exhibited in fog or conditions of reduced visibility.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Night Light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light which is only exhibited at night.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Light
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of different light types.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: All lights are considered to be marine lights unless the category of light indicates otherwise.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Directional Function
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light illuminating a sector of very narrow angle and intended to mark a direction to follow.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Leading Light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light associated with other lights so as to form a leading line to be followed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Aero Light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An aero light is established for aeronautical navigation and may be of higher power than marine lights and visible from well offshore.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Air Obstruction Light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light marking an obstacle which constitutes a danger to air navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flood Light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A broad beam light used to illuminate a structure or area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Strip Light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light whose source has a linear form generally horizontal, which can reach a length of several metres.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Subsidiary Light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light placed on or near the support of a main light and having a special use in navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spotlight
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A powerful light focused so as to illuminate a small area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Front
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Term used with leading lights to describe the position of the light on the lead as viewed from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rear
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Term used with leading lights to describe the position of the light on the lead as viewed from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lower
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Term used with leading lights to describe the position of the light on the lead as viewed from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Upper
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Term used with leading lights to describe the position of the light on the lead as viewed from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Emergency
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light available as a backup to a main light which will be illuminated should the main light fail.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bearing Light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light which enables its approximate bearing to be obtained without the use of a compass.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Horizontally Disposed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A group of lights of identical character and almost identical position, that are disposed horizontally.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Vertically Disposed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A group of lights of identical character and almost identical position, that are disposed vertically.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Traffic Flow
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Direction of vessels passing a reference point.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Inbound
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Traffic flow in a general direction toward a port or similar destination.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Outbound
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Traffic flow in a general direction away from a port or similar point of origin.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: One-Way
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Traffic flow in one general direction only.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Two-Way
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Traffic flow in two generally opposite directions.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Technique of Vertical Measurement
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Survey method used to obtain depth information.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Echo Sounder
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was determined by using an instrument that determines depth of water by measuring the time interval between emission of a sonic or ultrasonic signal and return of its echo from the bottom.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Side Scan Sonar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was computed from a record produced by active sonar in which fixed acoustic beams are directed into the water perpendicularly to the direction of travel to scan the seabed and generate a record of the seabed configuration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Multi Beam
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was determined by using a wide swath echo sounder that uses multiple beams to measure depths directly below and transverse to the ship's track.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Diver
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was determined by a person skilled in the practice of diving.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Lead Line
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was determined by using a line, graduated with attached marks and fastened to a sounding lead.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Swept by Wire-Drag
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The given area was determined to be free from navigational dangers to a certain depth by towing a buoyed wire at the desired depth by two launches, or a least depth was identified using the same technique.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Laser
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was determined by using an instrument that measures distance by emitting timed pulses of laser light and measuring the time between emission and reception of the reflected pulses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Swept by Vertical Acoustic System
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The given area has been swept using a system comprised of multiple echo sounder transducers attached to booms deployed from the survey vessel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Electromagnetic Sensor
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was determined by using an instrument that compares electromagnetic signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Photogrammetry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The science or art of obtaining reliable measurements from photographs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Satellite Imagery
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was determined by using instruments placed aboard an artificial satellite.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Levelling
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was determined by using levelling techniques to find the elevation of the point relative to a datum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Swept by Side Scan Sonar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The given area was determined to be free from navigational dangers to a certain depth by towing a side scan sonar.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Computer Generated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The sounding was determined from a bottom model constructed using a computer.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by LIDAR
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was measured by using an instrument that measures distance by emitting timed pulses of laser light and measuring the time between emission and reception of the reflected pulses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Synthetic Aperture Radar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A radar with a synthetic aperture antenna which is composed of a large number of elementary transducing elements. The signals are electronically combined into a resulting signal equivalent to that of a single antenna of a given aperture in a given direction.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hyperspectral Imagery
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Term used to describe the imagery derived from subdividing the electromagnetic spectrum into very narrow bandwidths. These narrow bandwidths may be combined with or subtracted from each other in various ways to form images useful in precise terrain or target analysis.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Quality of Vertical Measurement
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The reliability of the value of a sounding.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Depth Known
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth from the chart datum to the seabed (or to the top of a drying feature) is known.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Depth or Least Depth Unknown
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth from chart datum to the seabed, or the shoalest depth of the feature is unknown.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Doubtful Sounding
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A depth that may be less than indicated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unreliable Sounding
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A depth that is considered to be an unreliable value.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: No Bottom Found at Value Shown
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Upon investigation the bottom was not found at this depth.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Least Depth Known
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The shoalest depth over a feature is of known value.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Least Depth Unknown, Safe Clearance at Value Shown
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The least depth over a feature is unknown, but there is considered to be safe clearance at this depth.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Value Reported (Not Surveyed)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Depth value obtained from a report, but not fully surveyed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Value Reported (Not Confirmed)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Depth value obtained from a report, which it has not been possible to confirm.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Maintained Depth
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth at which a channel is kept by human influence, usually by dredging.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Not Regularly Maintained
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Depths may be altered by human influence, but will not be routinely maintained.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Maximal Permitted Draught
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The maximal permitted draught of a vessel or convoy according to the particular article/clause of the applicable law/regulation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Depth Range Minimum Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The minimum (shoalest) value of a depth range.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Where the area dries, the value is negative.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Based On Fixed Marks
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A straight route (known as a recommended track, range or leading line), which comprises: a. at least two structures (usually beacons or daymarks) and/or natural features, which may carry lights and/or top-marks. The structures/features are positioned so that when observed to be in line, a vessel can follow a known bearing with safety. (Adapted from International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities - IALA Aids to Navigation Guide, 1990); or b. a single structure or natural feature, which may carry lights and/or a topmark, and a specified bearing which can be followed with safety. (S-57 Edition 3.1, Appendix A Chapter 2, Page 2.72, November 2000, as amended).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Navigation Line
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of route guidance given to vessels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Clearing Line
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A straight line that marks the boundary between a safe and a dangerous area or that passes clear of a navigational danger.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Transit Line
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A line passing through one or more fixed marks.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Leading Line Bearing a Recommended Track
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A line passing through one or more clearly defined objects, along the path of which a vessel can approach safely up to a certain distance off.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Lateral Mark
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of lateral marks in the IALA Buoyage System.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: There are two international buoyage regions, A and B, between which lateral marks differ. When top-marks, retro reflectors and/or lights are fitted to these marks, they are encoded as separate features.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Port-Hand Lateral Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates the port boundary of a navigational channel or suggested route when proceeding in the "conventional direction of buoyage".

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Starboard-Hand Lateral Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates the starboard boundary of a navigational channel or suggested route when proceeding in the "conventional direction of buoyage".

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Preferred Channel to Starboard Lateral Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: At a point where a channel divides, when proceeding in the "conventional direction of buoyage", the preferred channel (or primary route) is indicated by a modified port-hand lateral mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Preferred Channel to Port Lateral Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: At a point where a channel divides, when proceeding in the "conventional direction of buoyage", the preferred channel (or primary route) is indicated by a modified starboard-hand lateral mark.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Manned Structure
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: An expression of the feature being permanently manned or not.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Datum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The reference level used for expressing the vertical measurements of points on the earth's surface. Also called datum level, reference plane, levelling datum, datum for sounding reduction, datum for heights.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the low waters of spring tides. This level is used as a tidal datum in some areas. Also called spring low water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Lower Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of lower low water springs at a place.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Sea Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the surface of the sea at a tide station for all stages of the tide over a 19-year period, usually determined from hourly height readings measured from a fixed predetermined reference level.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lowest Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level conforming to the lowest tide observed at a place, or some what lower.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of all low waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lowest Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level conforming to the lowest water level observed at a place at spring tides during a period of time shorter than 19 years.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Low Water Springs (MLWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Indian Spring Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary tidal datum approximating the level of the mean of the lower low water at spring tides. It was first used in waters surrounding India.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, approximating that of mean low water springs (MLWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Lowest Astronomical Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Lowest Astronomical Tide (LAT).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nearly Lowest Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level approximating the lowest water level observed at a place, usually equivalent to the Indian Spring Low Water (ISLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Lower Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the lower low waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The lowest level reached at a place by the water surface in one oscillation. Also called low tide.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Low Water (MLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Lower Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Lower Low Water (MLLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of all high waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean High Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the high waters of spring tides. Also called spring high water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The highest level reached at a place by the water surface in one oscillation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Sea Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Sea Level (MSL).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: High Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, approximating that of mean high water springs (MHWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Higher High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of higher high waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Equinoctial Spring Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The level of low water springs near the time of an equinox.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lowest Astronomical Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The lowest tide level which can be predicted to occur under average meteorological conditions and under any combination of astronomical conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Local Datum
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary datum defined by a local harbour authority, from which levels and tidal heights are measured by this authority.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: International Great Lakes Datum 1985
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A vertical reference system with its zero based on the mean water level at Rimouski/Pointe-au-Pere, Quebec, over the period 1970 to 1988.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Water Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average of all hourly water levels over the available period of record.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lower Low Water Large Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average of the lowest low waters, one from each of 19 years of observations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Higher High Water Large Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average of the highest high waters, one from each of 19 years of observations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nearly Highest High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level approximating the highest water level observed at a place, usually equivalent to the high water springs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Highest Astronomical Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The highest tidal level which can be predicted to occur under average meteorological conditions and under any combination of astronomical conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Local Low Water Reference Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Low water reference level of the local area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Local High Water Reference Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: High water reference level of the local area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Local Mean Water Reference Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Mean water reference level of the local area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Equivalent Height of Water (German GlW)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A low water level which is the result of a defined low water discharge - called "equivalent discharge".

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Highest Shipping Height of Water (German HSW)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Upper limit of water levels where navigation is allowed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Reference Low Water Level According to Danube Commission
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The water level at a discharge, which is exceeded 94 % of the year within a period of 30 years.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Highest Shipping Height of Water According to Danube Commission
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The water level at a discharge, which is exceeded 1% of the year within a period of 30 years.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dutch River Low Water Reference Level (OLR)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The water level at a discharge, which is exceeded 95% of the year within a period of 20 years.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Russian Project Water Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Conditional low water level with established probability.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Russian Normal Backwater Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Highest water level derived from the upper backwater stream in watercourse or reservoir under the normal operational conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ohio River Datum
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The Ohio River datum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dutch High Water Reference Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Dutch High Water Reference Level.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Baltic Sea Chart Datum 2000
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The datum refers to each Baltic country's realization of the European Vertical Reference System (EVRS) with land-uplift epoch 2000, which is connected to the Normaal Amsterdams Peil (NAP).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dutch Estuary Low Water Reference Level (OLW)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Dutch Estuary Low Water Reference Level (OLW)

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Function
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A specific role that describes a feature.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Harbour-Masters Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A local official who has charge of mooring and berthing of vessels, collecting harbour fees, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Customs Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Serves as a government office where customs duties are collected, the flow of goods are regulated and restrictions enforced, and shipments or vehicles are cleared for entering or leaving a country.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Health Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The office which is charged with the administration of health laws and sanitary inspections.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hospital
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An institution or establishment providing medical or surgical treatment for the ill or wounded.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Post Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The public department, agency or organisation responsible primarily for the collection, transmission and distribution of mail.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hotel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An establishment, especially of a comfortable or luxurious kind, where paying visitors are provided with accommodation, meals and other services.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Railway Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building with platforms where trains arrive, load, discharge and depart.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Police Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The headquarters of a local police force and that is where those under arrest are first charged.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Water-Police Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The headquarters of a local water-police force.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pilot Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The office or headquarters of pilots; the place where the services of a pilot may be obtained.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pilot Lookout
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A distinctive structure or place on shore from which personnel keep watch upon events at sea or along the coast.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bank Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An office for custody, deposit, loan, exchange or issue of money.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Headquarters for District Control
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The quarters of an executive officer (director, manager, etc.) with responsibility for an administrative area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Transit Shed/Warehouse
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building or part of a building for storage of wares or goods.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Factory
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building or buildings with equipment for manufacturing; a workshop.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Power Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A stationary plant containing apparatus for large scale conversion of some form of energy (such as hydraulic, steam, chemical or nuclear energy) into electrical energy.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Administrative
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building for the management of affairs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Educational Facility
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building concerned with education (for example school, college, university, etc).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Church
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building for public Christian worship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Chapel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place for Christian worship other than a parish, cathedral or church, especially one attached to a private house or institution.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Temple
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building for public Jewish worship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pagoda
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A Hindu or Buddhist temple or sacred building.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Shinto Shrine
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building for public Shinto worship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buddhist Temple
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building for public Buddhist worship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mosque
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A Muslim place of worship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Marabout
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A shrine marking the burial place of a Muslim holy man.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lookout
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Keeping a watch upon events at sea or along the coast.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Communication
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Transmitting and/or receiving electronic communication signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Television
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A system for reproducing on a screen visual images transmitted (usually with sound) by radio signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Radio
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Transmitting and/or receiving radio-frequency electromagnetic waves as a means of communication.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Radar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A method, system or technique of using beamed, reflected, and timed radio waves for detecting, locating, or tracking objects, and for measuring altitudes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Light Support
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure serving as a support for one or more lights.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Microwave
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Broadcasting and receiving signals using microwaves.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cooling
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Generation of chilled liquid and/or gas for cooling purposes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Observation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place from which the surroundings can be observed but at which a watch is not habitually maintained.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Timeball
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A visual time signal in the form of a ball.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Clock
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Instrument for measuring time and recording hours.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Control
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Used to control the flow of traffic within a specified range of an installation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Airship Mooring
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Equipment or structure to secure an airship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stadium
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arena for holding and viewing events.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bus Station
