S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building where buses and coaches regularly stop to take on and/or let off passengers, especially for long-distance travel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Passenger Terminal Building
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building within a terminal for the loading and unloading of passengers.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sea Rescue Control
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A unit responsible for promoting efficient organization of search and rescue services and for coordinating the conduct of search and rescue operations within a search and rescue region.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Observatory
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building designed and equipped for making observations of astronomical, meteorological, or other natural phenomena.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ore Crusher
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building or structure used to crush ore.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Boathouse
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building or shed, usually built partly over water, for sheltering a boat or boats.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pumping Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A facility to move solids, liquids or gases by means of pressure or suction.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Landmark
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of prominent cultural and natural features in the landscape.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cairn
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mound of stones, usually conical or pyramidal, raised as a landmark or to designate a point of importance in surveying.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cemetery
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A site and associated structures devoted to the burial of the dead.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Chimney
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A vertical structure containing a passage or flue for discharging smoke and gases of combustion.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dish Aerial
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A parabolic aerial for the receipt and transmission of high frequency radio signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flagstaff
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A staff or pole on which flags are raised.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flare Stack
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tall structure used for burning-off waste oil or gas.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mast
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A relatively tall structure usually held vertical by guy lines.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Windsock
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tapered fabric sleeve mounted so as to catch and swing with the wind, thus indicating the wind direction.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Monument
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure erected and/or maintained as a memorial to a person and/or event.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Column/Pillar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A cylindrical or slightly tapering body of considerably greater length than diameter erected vertically.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Memorial Plaque
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A slab of metal, usually ornamented, erected as a memorial to a person or event.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Obelisk
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tapering shaft usually of stone or concrete, square or rectangular in section, with a pyramidal apex.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Statue
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A representation of a living being, sculptured, moulded, or cast in a variety of materials (for example: marble, metal, or plaster).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cross
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A monument, or other structure in form of a cross.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dome
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A landmark comprising a hemispherical or spheroidal shaped structure.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Radar Scanner
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A device used for directing a radar beam through a search pattern.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Tower
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A relatively tall, narrow structure that may either stand alone or may form part of another structure.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Windmill
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A system of vanes attached to a tower and driven by wind (excluding wind turbines).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Windmotor
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A modern structure for the use of wind power.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spire/Minaret
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tall conical or pyramid-shaped structure often built on the roof or tower of a building, especially a church or mosque.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Large Rock or Boulder on Land
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An isolated rocky formation or a single large stone.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Triangulation Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A recoverable point on the earth, whose geographic position has been determined by angular methods with geodetic instruments. A triangulation point is a selected point, which has been marked with a station mark, or it is a conspicuous natural or artificial feature.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Boundary Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A marker identifying the location of a surveyed boundary line.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Observation Wheel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Wheels with passenger cars mounted external to the rim and independently rotated by electric motors.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Torii
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A form of decorative gateway or portal, consisting of two upright wooden posts connected at the top by two horizontal crosspieces, commonly found at the entrance to Shinto temples.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bridge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (1) An elevated structure extending across or over the weather deck of a vessel, or part of such a structure. The term is sometimes modified to indicate the intended use, such as navigating bridge or signal bridge. (2) A structure erected over a depression or an obstacle such as a body of water, railroad, etc., to provide a roadway for vehicles or pedestrians.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dam
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A barrier to check or confine anything in motion; particularly one constructed to hold back water and raise its level to form a reservoir, or to prevent flooding.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Type of Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Type equipment used as a buoy in a particular installation.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Types of light buoy; for example LANBY-100, LS-35, LL-30, LL-28, LL-26, LL-26(M), LL-24, LS-24, LSP-24, LT-10Types of buoy e.g. U-17C(P), U-17S(P), U-17C(S), U-17S(S), UR-17C(P), UR-17S(P), UR-17C(S), UR-17.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Buoy Shape
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The principal shape and/or design of a buoy.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The principal shapes are those recommended in the International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities - IALA System.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Conical
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has approximately the shape or the appearance of a pointed cone with the point upwards.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Can
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has the shape of a cylinder, or a truncated cone that approximates to a cylinder, with a flat end uppermost.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spherical
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Shaped like a sphere, which is a body the surface of which is at all points equidistant from the centre.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pillar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure is a narrow vertical structure, pillar or lattice tower.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has the form of a pole, or of a very long cylinder, floating upright.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Barrel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has the form of a barrel or cylinder floating horizontally.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Superbuoy
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A very large buoy designed to carry a signal light of high luminous intensity at a high elevation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ice Buoy
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specially constructed shuttle shaped buoy which is used in ice conditions.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Visual Prominence
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The extent to which a feature, either natural or artificial, is visible from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Visually Conspicuous
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Term applied to a feature either natural or artificial which is distinctly and notably visible from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Not Visually Conspicuous
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An object that may be visible from seaward, but cannot be used as a fixing mark and is not conspicuous.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Prominent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Objects which are easily identifiable, but do not justify being classed as conspicuous.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Length
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The total vertical length of a feature.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: For floating objects: the vertical distance from the surface of water to the highest point of that object. For fixed objects: the vertical distance from seabed or ground to the highest point of that object. For objects on top of other objects: the vertical distance from the lowest to the highest point of that object. Vertical length measurements do not require a datum.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Status
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The condition of an object at a given instant in time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Permanent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Intended to last or function indefinitely.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Occasional
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Acting on special occasions; happening irregularly.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Recommended
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Presented as worthy of confidence, acceptance, use, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Not in Use
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Use has ceased, but the facility still exists intact; disused.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Periodic/Intermittent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Recurring at intervals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Reserved
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Set apart for some specific use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Temporary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Meant to last only for a time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Private
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Administered by an individual or corporation, rather than a State or a public body.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mandatory
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Compulsory; enforced.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Extinguished
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: No longer lit.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Illuminated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Lit by floodlights, strip lights, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Historic
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Famous in history; of historical interest.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Public
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Belonging to, available to, used or shared by, the community as a whole and not restricted to private use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Synchronized
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Occur at a time, coincide in point of time, be contemporary or simultaneous.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Watched
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Looked at or observed over a period of time especially so as to be aware of any movement or change.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unwatched
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Usually automatic in operation, without any permanently-stationed personnel to superintend it.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Existence Doubtful
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A feature that has been reported but has not been definitely determined to exist.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: On Request
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: When you ask for it.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Drop Away
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: To become lower in level.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rising
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: To become higher in level.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Increasing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Becoming larger in magnitude.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Decreasing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Becoming smaller in magnitude.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Strong
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Not easily broken or destroyed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Good
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: In a satisfactory condition to use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Moderately
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Fairly but not very.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Poor
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Not as good as it could be or should.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoyed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Marked by buoys.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fully Operational
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Entire observation platform is operating in accordance with, or exceeding, manufacturer specifications.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Partially Operational
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: At least one instrument that is part of an observation platform is not operating to manufacturer specification.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Drifting
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Floating platform at the mercy of environmental elements, whether intentional or not.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Broken
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Fractured or in pieces.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Offline
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Observation platform is intentionally not reporting an environmental observation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Discontinued
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Observation station, suite of instruments, or an individual instrument, for a particular location, has been removed and is no longer at the particular location.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Manual Observation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Observations made by a human observer.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unknown Status
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Status of an observation platform, suite of instruments, or individual instrument is not known or unspecified.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Confirmed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Made certain as to truth, accuracy, validity, availability, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Candidate
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Item selected for an action.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Under Modification
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Item that is in the process of being modified.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Under Removal / Deletion
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Item in the process of being removed or deleted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Removed / Deleted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Item that has been removed or deleted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Candidate for Modification
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Item selected for modification.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Radar Conspicuous
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A feature which returns a strong radar echo.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Nature of Construction
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The building's primary construction material.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Masonry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed of stones or bricks, usually quarried, shaped, and mortared.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Concreted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed of concrete, a material made of sand and gravel that is united by cement into a hardened mass used for roads, foundations, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Loose Boulders
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from large stones or blocks of concrete, often placed loosely for protection against waves or water turbulence.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hard Surfaced
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed with a surface of hard material, usually a term applied to roads surfaced with asphalt or concrete.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unsurfaced
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed with no extra protection, usually a term applied to roads not surfaced with a hard material.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wooden
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from wood.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Metal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from metal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Glass Reinforced Plastic
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from a plastic material strengthened with fibres of glass.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Painted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The application of paint to some other construction or natural feature.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Framework
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from a lattice framework of, often diagonal, intersecting struts.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Latticed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure of crossed wooden or metal strips usually arranged to form a diagonal pattern of open spaces between the strips.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Glass
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: [1] Any artificial or natural substance having similar properties and composition, as fused borax, obsidian, or the like. [2] Something made of such a substance, as a windowpane.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fiberglass
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from fiberglass.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Plastic
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from plastic.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Marks Navigational - System Of
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The system of navigational buoyage a region complies with.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: IALA A
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to the International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities - IALA A system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: IALA B
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to the International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities - IALA B system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: No System
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids do not conform to any defined system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Other System
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to a defined system other than International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities - IALA.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: CEVNI
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: CEVNI (European Code for Navigation on Inland Waterways) is the European code for rivers, canals land lakes in most of Europe.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Russian Inland Waterway Regulations
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to the Russian inland waterway regulations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Brazilian National Inland Waterway Regulations - Two Sides
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to the Brazilian national inland waterway regulations for two sides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Brazilian National Inland Waterway Regulations - Side Independent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to the Brazilian national inland waterway regulations - side independent.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Paraguay-Parana Waterway - Brazilian Complementary Aids
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to the Brazilian complementary aids on the Paraguay-Parana waterway.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Height
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The value of the vertical distance to the highest point of the object, measured from a specified vertical datum.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Height must not be used for floating objects.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Elevation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The altitude of the ground level of an object, measured from a specified vertical datum.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Colour Pattern
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A regular repeated design containing more than one colour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Horizontal Stripes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented horizontally.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Vertical Stripes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented vertically.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Diagonal Stripes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented diagonally (that is, not horizontally or vertically).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Squared
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Often referred to as checker plate, where alternate colours are used to create squares similar to a chess or draught board. The pattern may be straight or diagonal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stripes (Direction Unknown)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented in an unknown direction.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Border Stripe
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A band or stripe of colour which is displayed around the outer edge of the object, which may also form a border to an inner pattern or plain colour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Single Colour
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: One solid colour of uniform coverage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rectangle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A four-sided shape that is made up of two pairs of parallel lines and that has four right angles, on a different coloured background.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Triangle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A shape that is made up of three lines and three angles, on a different coloured background.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Colour
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The property possessed by an object of producing different sensations on the eye as a result of the way it reflects or emits light.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: White
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The achromatic object colour of greatest lightness characteristically perceived to belong to objects that reflect diffusely nearly all incident energy throughout the visible spectrum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Black
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The achromatic color of least lightness characteristically perceived to belong to objects that neither reflect nor transmit light.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Red
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A color whose hue resembles that of blood or of the ruby or is that of the long-wave extreme of the visible spectrum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Green
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Of the color green.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Blue
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A color whose hue is that of the clear sky or that of the portion of the color spectrum lying between green and violet.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Yellow
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A color whose hue resembles that of ripe lemons or sunflowers or is that of the portion of the spectrum lying between green and orange.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Grey
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Of the color grey.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Brown
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any of a group of colors between red and yellow in hue, of medium to low lightness, and of moderate to low saturation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Amber
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A variable color averaging a dark orange yellow.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Violet
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any of a group of colors of reddish-blue hue, low lightness, and medium saturation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Orange
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any of a group of colors that are between red and yellow in hue.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Magenta
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A deep purplish red.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pink
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any of a group of colors bluish red to red in hue, of medium to high lightness, and of low to moderate saturation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Beacon Shape
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Describes the characteristic geometric form of the beacon.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stake, Pole, Perch, Post
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An elongated wood or metal pole, driven into the ground or seabed, which serves as a navigational aid or a support for a navigational aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Withy
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tree without roots stuck or spoiled into the bottom of the sea to serve as a navigational aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Beacon Tower
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A solid structure of the order of 10 metres in height used as a navigational aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lattice Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure consisting of strips of metal or wood crossed or interlaced to form a structure to serve as an aid to navigation or as a support for an aid to navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pile Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A long heavy timber(s) or section(s) of steel, wood, concrete, etc., forced into the seabed to serve as an aid to navigation or as a support for an aid to navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cairn
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mound of stones, usually conical or pyramidal, raised as a landmark or to designate a point of importance in surveying.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoyant Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tall spar-like beacon fitted with a permanently submerged buoyancy chamber, the lower end of the body is secured to seabed sinker either by a flexible joint or by a cable under tension.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date Start
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The earliest date on which an object (for example a buoy) will be present.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The Date Start should be encoded using 4 digits for the calendar year (YYYY), 2 digits for the month (MM) (for example April = 04) and 2 digits for the day (DD). When no specific month and/or day is required/known, indication of the month and/or day is omitted, and replaced with dashes (-). When no specific year is required (that is, the event or date range ends at the same time each year) the following two cases may be considered:- same day each year: ----MMDD- same month each year: ----MM--This conforms to ISO 8601: 2004. Date Start indicates the earliest date of an event or the start of a date range. It is used to indicate the start of a fixed date range, the start of a periodic date range, or the deployment or implementation of a feature at a specific date in the future.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date End
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The latest date on which an object (for example a buoy) will be present.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The Date End should be encoded using 4 digits for the calendar year (YYYY), 2 digits for the month (MM) (for example April = 04) and 2 digits for the day (DD). When no specific month and/or day is required/known, indication of the month and/or day is omitted, and replaced with dashes (-). When no specific year is required (that is, the event or date range ends at the same time each year) the following two cases may be considered:- same day each year: ----MMDD- same month each year: ----MM--This conforms to ISO 8601: 2004. Date End indicates the latest date of an event or the end of a date range. It is used to indicate the end of a fixed date range, the end of a periodic date range, or the removal or cancellation of a feature at a specific date in the future.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Installation Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The date when an item was installed.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: AtoN Number
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Identifier from a list of Aids to Navigation publication, such as List of Lights.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: ID Code
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Identification code as specified in predefined system. Also called identification number.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Scale Minimum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The minimum scale at which the feature may be used for example for ECDIS presentation.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The modulus of the scale is indicated, that is 1:1 250 000 is encoded as 1250000.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Source Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The production date of the source; for example the date of measurement.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Source
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The publication, document, or reference work from which information comes or is acquired.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: May be populated with the corresponding paper chart Notice to Mariners numbers, although other references are permitted.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Pictorial Representation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Indicates whether a pictorial representation of the feature is available.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The 'pictorial representation' could be a drawing or a photo. The string encodes the file name of an external graphic file (pixel/vector).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Inspection Frequency
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement of how frequently an item is inspected.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Inspection Requirements
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement of what requirements are in place for how inspection of an item is carried out.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: AtoN Maintenance Record
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A reference following the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) principles to a record of maintenance.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Display Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement expressing if a feature name is to be displayed in certain system display settings or not.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Where it is allowable to encode multiple instances of feature name for a single feature instance, only one feature name instance can indicate that the name is to be displayed (display name set to True).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The individual name of a feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Aid Availability Category
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A Category denoting the significance of an Aid to Navigation, expressed in terms of the probability that an AtoN or system of AtoN, as defined by the Competent Authority, is performing its specified function at any randomly chosen time. This is expressed as a percentage of total time that an AtoN or system of AtoN should be performing their specified function.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Category 1
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An AtoN or system of AtoN that is considered by the Competent Authority to be of vital navigational significance.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Category 2
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An AtoN or system of AtoN that is considered by the Competent Authority to be of important navigational significance.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Category 3
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An AtoN or system of AtoN that is considered by the Competent Authority to be of necessary navigational significance.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Condition
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The various conditions of buildings and other constructions.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The default 'condition' should be considered to be completed, undamaged and working normally.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Under Construction
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Being built but not yet capable of function.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ruined
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure in a decayed or deteriorated condition resulting from neglect or disuse, or a damaged structure in need of repair.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Under Reclamation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area of the sea, a lake or the navigable part of a river that is being reclaimed as land, usually by the dumping of earth and other material.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wingless
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A windmill or wind turbine from which the vanes or turbine blades are missing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Planned Construction
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Detailed planning has been completed but construction has not been initiated.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Remote Monitoring System
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification or name of system used to remotely monitor a feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Delivery Point
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Details of where post can be delivered such as the apartment, name and/or number of a street, building or PO Box.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: City Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The name of a town or city.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Administrative Division
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A generic term for an administrative region within a country at a level below that of the sovereign state.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Country Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The name of a nation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Postal Code
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Known in various countries as a postcode, or ZIP code, the postal code is a series of letters and/or digits that identifies each postal delivery area.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category Of Aggregation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: named aggregations between two or more aids to navigation and/or navigationally relevant features

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Text
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A non-formatted digital text string.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Should be used, for example, to hold the information that is for short cautionary or explanatory notes. Therefore, text populated in text must not exceed 300 characters. Text may be in English, or in a national language. No formatting of text is possible within text. If formatted text, or text strings exceeding 300 characters, is required, then an alternate concept should be used.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Language
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The method of human communication, either spoken or written, consisting of the use of words in a structured and conventional way.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The language is encoded by a 3 character code following ISO 639-2/T.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Headline
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Words set at the head of a passage or page to introduce or categorize.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Reference
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The file name of an externally referenced text file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Locator
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The location of a fragment of text or other information in a support file.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Application schemas must describe how the associated file is identified. The associated file will commonly be named in a file reference co-attribute of the same complex attribute. Each DCEG must specify requirements for the format of the associated file and the semantics of file locator. For example, the value of file locator may be an HTML ID in an HTML file, line number in a text file) or a bookmark in a PDF file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Uncertainty Variable Factor
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The factor to be applied to the variable component of an uncertainty equation so as to provide the best estimate of the variable horizontal or vertical accuracy component for positions, depths, heights, vertical distances and vertical clearances.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Uncertainty Fixed
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the fixed horizontal or vertical accuracy component for positions, depths, heights, vertical distances and vertical clearances.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Information in National Language
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Textual information in national language characters.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Encodes any textual information about an object using a specified national language. The textual information could be, for example, a list, a table or a text. This should be used, for example, to hold the information that is shown on paper charts by cautionary and explanatory notes.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Distance Uncertainty
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the horizontal accuracy of horizontal clearances and distances.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The error is assumed to be positive and negative. The plus/minus character must not be encoded.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Orientation Uncertainty
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the accuracy of a bearing.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Temporal Variation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: An assessment of the likelihood of change over time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Extreme Event
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indication of the possible impact of a significant event (for example hurricane, earthquake, volcanic eruption, landslide, etc), which is considered likely to have changed the seafloor or landscape significantly.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Likely to Change and Significant Shoaling Expected
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Continuous or frequent change (for example river siltation, sand waves, seasonal storms, icebergs, etc) that is likely to result in new significant shoaling.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Likely to Change But Significant Shoaling Not Expected
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Continuous or frequent change (for example sand wave shift, seasonal storms, icebergs, etc) that is not likely to result in new significant shoaling.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Likely to Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Continuous or frequent change to non-bathymetric features (for example river siltation, glacier creep/recession, sand dunes, buoys, marine farms, etc).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unlikely to Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Significant change to the seafloor is not expected.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unassessed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Not having been assessed.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Maximum Display Scale
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The value considered by the Data Producer to be the maximum (largest) scale at which the data is to be displayed before it can be considered to be grossly overscaled.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Minimum Display Scale
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The smallest intended viewing scale for the data.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Front leading/range light Light range reduced
Rear leading/range light Light range reduced
Front leading/range light is operating properly
Rear leading/range light is operating properly
Front leading/range beacon restored to normal
Rear leading/range beacon restored to normal

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Contact Address
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Direction or superscription of a letter, package, etc., specifying the name of the place to which it is directed, and optionally a contact person or organisation who should receive it.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Directional Character
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A directional light is a light illuminating a sector of very narrow angle and intended to mark a direction to follow.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Feature Name
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Provides the name of an entity, defines the national language of the name, and provides the option to display the name at various system display settings.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Fixed Date Range
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: An active period of a single fixed event or occurrence, as the date range between discrete start and end dates.
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Dates must be encoded in the format YYYYMMDD; using 4 digits for the calendar year (YYYY) and, optionally, 2 digits for the month (MM) (for example April = 04) and 2 digits for the day (DD). When no specific month and/or day is required/known, the values are replaced with dashes (-). The date range of a recurring event or occurrence must be encoded using periodicDateRange.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Light Sector
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A sector is the part of a circle between two straight lines drawn from the centre to the circumference.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Multiplicity of Features
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The number of features of identical character that exist as a colocated group.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Orientation
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: (1) The angular distance measured from true north to the major axis of the feature. (2) In ECDIS, the mode in which information on the ECDIS is being presented. Typical modes include: north-up - as shown on a nautical chart, north is at the top of the display; Ships head-up - based on the actual heading of the ship, (e.g. Ships gyrocompass); course-up display - based on the course or route being taken.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Periodic Date Range
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The active period of a recurring event or occurrence.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Radar Wave Length
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The distance between two successive peaks (or other points of identical phase) on an electromagnetic wave in the radar band of the electromagnetic spectrum.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Rhythm of Light
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The sequence of times occupied by intervals of light/sound and eclipse/silence for all light characteristics or sound signals.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector Characteristics
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Describes the characteristics of a light sector.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector Information
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Additional textual information about a light sector.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector Limit
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A sector is the part of a circle between two straight lines drawn from the centre to the circumference. The sector limit specifies the limits of the sector In a clockwise direction around the central feature (for example a light).

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector Limit One
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A sector is the part of a circle between two straight lines drawn from the centre to the circumference. Sector limit one specifies the first limit of the sector. The order of sector limit one and sector limit two is clockwise around the central feature (for example a light).

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector Limit Two
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A sector is the part of a circle between two straight lines drawn from the centre to the circumference. Sector limit two specifies the second limit of the sector. The order of sector limit one and sector limit two is clockwise around the central feature (for example a light).

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Shape Information
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Textual information about the shape of a non-standard topmark.
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:remarks: No formatting of text is possible within shape information. If formatted text is required, then an associated text file referenced by the complex attribute textual description must be used.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal Sequence
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The sequence of times occupied by intervals of light and eclipse for all light characteristics.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Spatial Accuracy
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Provides an indication of the vertical and horizontal positional uncertainty of bathymetric data, optionally within a specified date range.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Cable Dimensions
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The dimensions of a cable to give its length and diameter.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Sinker Dimensions
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The dimensions of a sinker/anchor to give its three dimensional shape measurements.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Positioning Method
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A description of the method used to obtain a position.(proposed by CCG)

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Position Uncertainty
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the accuracy of a position.
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The expected input is the maximum of the two-dimensional error. The error is assumed to be positive and negative.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Information
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Textual information about the feature. The information may be provided as a string of text or as a file name of a single external text file that contains the text.
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:remarks: At least one of the sub-attributes file reference or text must be populated.The sub-attribute file reference is generally used for long text strings or those that require formatting, however, there is no restriction on the type of text (except for lexical level) that can be held in files referenced by sub-attribute file reference.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Textual Description
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Encodes the file name of a single external text file that contains the text in a defined language, which provides additional textual information that cannot be provided using other allowable attributes for the feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Uncertainty
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the vertical accuracy of depths, heights, vertical distances and vertical clearances.
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Encodes the vertical uncertainty associated with any vertical measurement.

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: Navigable Track
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: The role given to the navigable part of the navigation line.

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: Navigation Line
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: The role given to the navigation line(s) that is generally formed between two or more objects, or by one object and a bearing.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: AtoN Fixing Method
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: Method used for fixing the position of an aid to navigation.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: Positioning Information
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: Information about how a position was obtained. (proposed by CCG)

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: Spatial Quality
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: The indication of the quality of the locational information for features in a dataset.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Aids to Navigation
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A visual, acoustical, or radio device, external to a ship, designed to assist in determining a safe course or a vessel's position, or to warn of dangers and/or obstructions. Aids to navigation usually include buoys, beacons, fog signals, lights, radio beacons, leading marks, radio position fixing systems and GNSS which are chart-related and assist safe navigation.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Structure Object
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: Something (such as a house, tower, bridge, etc.) that is built by putting parts together and that usually stands on its own.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Equipment
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: The implements used in an operation or activity.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Electronic Aton
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: TBD

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Generic Beacon
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A fixed artificial navigation mark that can be recognized by its shape, colour, pattern, topmark or light character, or a combination of these. It may carry various additional aids to navigation.
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:remarks: This term is not commonly used when the navigation mark can be classified as a lighthouse.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Generic Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A floating object moored to the bottom in a particular (charted) place, as an aid to navigation or for other specific purposes.
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:remarks: Navigational buoys may be classified according to: (a) their shape, appearance, or construction, such as barrel, can, cask, conical, cylindrical, dan, keg, nun, pillar, spar, spherical,or topmark buoy; (b) their colour, such as black, chequered, green, red buoy; (c) their location, such as bifurcation, fairway, junction, mid-channel, middle-ground, or turning buoy; (d) the various kinds of hazards or dangers to navigation which they mark, such as bar, isolated danger, fish trap, obstruction, spoil ground, telegraph or wreck buoy; (e) their particular purpose or use, such as anchor, anchorage, compass adjustment, dredging, farewell (or landfall), marker, quarantine, station (or watch), or warping buoy.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Landmark
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A prominent object at a fixed location on land which can be used in determining a location or a direction.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Lateral Beacon
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A lateral beacon is used to indicate the port or starboard hand side of the route to be followed. They are generally used for well defined channels and are used in conjunction with a conventional direction of buoyage.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Lateral Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A lateral buoy is used to indicate the port or starboard hand side of the route to be followed. They are generally used for well-defined channels and are used in conjunction with a conventional direction of buoyage.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Navigation Line
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A straight line extending towards an area of navigational interest and generally generated by two navigational aids or one navigational aid and a bearing.
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:remarks: The extent of the navigation line depends on the visibility of the navigational aid(s). The recommended track is that portion of a 'navigation line' that a ship should use for navigation.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Recommended Track
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A route which has been specially examined to ensure so far as possible that it is free of dangers and along which ships are advised to navigate.
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:remarks: Recommended tracks include all channels recommended for hydrographic reasons to lead safely between shoal depths. The use of such tracks is generally left to the discretion of the mariner and will depend on the vessel's draught, the state of the tide, adequacy of navigational aids and so on (IHO Chart Specifications, M-4). The recommended track is that portion of a 'navigation line' that a ship should use for navigation. In the case of a two-way recommended track only one value of orientation is encoded; the other value can be deduced (that is, the value encoded + 180 degrees).

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Light Sectored
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A light presenting different appearances (in particular, different colours) over various parts of the horizon of interest to maritime navigation.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Light All Around
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An all around light is a light that is visible over the whole horizon of interest to marine navigation and having no change in the characteristics of the light.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Light Air Obstruction
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An air obstruction light is a light marking an obstacle which constitutes a danger to air navigation.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Light Fog Detector
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A fog detector light is a light used to automatically determine conditions of visibility which warrant the turning on or off of a sound signal.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Radar Reflector
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A device capable of, or intended for, reflecting radar signals.
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:remarks: A radar reflector is usually a tetrahedron or pentagonal corner reflector to facilitate reflection towards the sender (International Maritime Dictionary, 2nd Ed.).

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Fog Signal
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A warning signal transmitted by a vessel, or aid to navigation, during periods of low visibility. Also, the device producing such a signal.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Environment Observation Equipment
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A sensor used to observe the environment.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Radio Station
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A place equipped to transmit radio waves. Such a station may be either stationary or mobile, and may also be provided with a radio receiver.
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:remarks: The transmission of a radio station may serve to provide mariners with a line of position (IHO Chart Specifications, M-4). The feature 'radio station' is used to encode the point of transmission of the signal.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Daymark
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: (1) The identifying characteristics of an aid to navigation which serve to facilitate its recognition against a daylight viewing background. On those structures that do not by themselves present an adequate viewing area to be seen at the required distance, the aid is made more visible by affixing a daymark to the structure. A daymark so affixed has a distinctive colour and shape depending on the purpose of the aid. (2) An unlighted navigational mark.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Retroreflector
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A means of distinguishing unlighted marks at night. Retro-reflective material is secured to the mark in a particular pattern to reflect back light.
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:remarks: The body carrying the retro-reflector is a separate feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Radar Transponder Beacon
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A transponder beacon transmitting a coded signal on radar frequency, permitting an interrogating craft to determine the bearing and range of the transponder.
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:remarks: The feature 'radar transponder beacon' is only used to encode the technical equipment independent of the structure on which it is located (for example a beacon, light-vessel or tower).

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Virtual AIS Aid to Navigation
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An Automatic Identification System (AIS) message 21 transmitted from an AIS station to simulate on navigation systems an Aid to Navigation which does not physically exist.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Physical AIS Aid to Navigation
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An Automatic Identification System (AIS) message 21 transmitted from a physical Aid to Navigation, or transmitted from an AIS station for an Aid to Navigation which physically exists.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Isolated Danger Beacon
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An isolated danger beacon is a beacon erected on an isolated danger of limited extent, which has navigable water all around it.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Cardinal Beacon
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A cardinal beacon is used in conjunction with the compass to indicate where the mariner may find the best navigable water. It is placed in one of the four quadrants (North, East, South and West), bounded by inter-cardinal bearings from the point marked.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Isolated Danger Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An isolated danger buoy is a buoy moored on or above an isolated danger of limited extent, which has navigable water all around it.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Cardinal Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A cardinal buoy is used in conjunction with the compass to indicate where the mariner may find the best navigable water. It is placed in one of the four quadrants (North, East, South and West), bounded by inter-cardinal bearings from the point marked.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Installation Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A buoy is a floating object moored to the bottom in a particular place, as an aid to navigation or for other specific purposes. (IHO Dictionary, S-32, 5th Edition, 565). An installation buoy is a buoy used for loading tankers with gas or oil. (IHO Chart Specifications, M-4)

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Mooring Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: The equipment or structure used to secure a vessel. (IHO Registry)

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Emergency Wreck Marking Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An emergency wreck marking buoy is a buoy moored on or above a new wreck, designed to provide a prominent (both visual and radio) and easily identifiable temporary (24-72 hours) first response. (IHO Registry)

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Lighthouse
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A distinctive structure on or off a coast exhibiting a major light designed to serve as an aid to navigation.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Light Float
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A boat-like structure used instead of a light buoy in waters where strong streams or currents are experienced, or when a greater elevation than that of a light buoy is necessary.
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:remarks: The light of a light float is a separate feature, handled as with buoys, beacons, etc.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Light Vessel
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A distinctively marked vessel anchored or moored at a charted point, to serve as an aid to navigation. By night, it displays a characteristic light(s) and is usually equipped with other devices, such as fog signal, submarine sound signal, and radio-beacon, to assist navigation.
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:remarks: The light(s), fog signal etc. of a light vessel are separate features, handled as with buoys, beacons, etc.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Offshore Platform
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A permanent offshore structure, either fixed or floating.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Silo/Tank
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A large storage structure used for storing loose materials, liquids and/or gases.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Pile
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A long heavy timber or section of steel, wood, concrete, etc., forced into the earth or sea floor to serve as a support, as for a pier, or to resist lateral pressure; or as a free standing pole within a marine environment.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Building
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A free-standing self-supporting construction that is roofed, usually walled, and is intended for human occupancy (for example: a place of work or recreation) and/or habitation.
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:remarks: This feature is used to encode single buildings, including those with a particular function or service of major interest.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Bridge
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: (1) An elevated structure extending across or over the weather deck of a vessel, or part of such a structure. The term is sometimes modified to indicate the intended use, such as navigating bridge or signal bridge. (2) A structure erected over a depression or an obstacle such as a body of water, railroad, etc., to provide a roadway for vehicles or pedestrians.
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:remarks: A bridge may consist of portions which cover the land and the water.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Sinker Anchor
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A heavy weight (of concrete, cast-iron, etc..) that rests on the sea bed and to which a mooring line can be attached. (IALA Dictionary, 8-5-025)

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Mooring Shackle
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A shackle at the lower end of a mooring chain, for attachment to an anchor or sinker. (IALA Dictionary, 8-5-150)

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Cable Submarine
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An assembly of wires or fibres, or a wire rope or chain, which has been laid underwater or buried beneath the sea floor.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Swivel
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A chain link that provides for rotary motion between the lengths of chain that it connects. (IALA Dictionary, 8-5-165)

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Bridle
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: Two lengths of chain connected by a central ring and used for lifting wide loads. (IALA Dictionary,8-3-195)

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Topmark
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A characteristic shape secured at the top of a buoy or beacon to aid in its identification. (IHO Dictionary, S-32, 5th Edition, 5548)

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Safe Water Beacon
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A safe water beacon is used to indicate that there is navigable water around the mark.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Special Purpose General Beacon
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A special purpose beacon is primarily used to indicate an area or feature, the nature of which is apparent from reference to a chart, Sailing Directions or Notices to Mariners.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Safe Water Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A safe water buoy is used to indicate that there is navigable water around the mark.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Special Purpose General Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A special purpose buoy is primarily used to indicate an area or feature, the nature of which is apparent from reference to a chart, Sailing Directions or Notices to Mariners.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Aton Aggregation
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: Used to identify an aggregation of two or more objects. This aggregation may be named content of categoryOfAggregation should be put in information attribute when converting to S-57.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Aton Association
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: Used to identify an association between two or more objects. The association may be named content of categoryOfAssociation should be put in information attribute when converting to S-57

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Quality of Non-Bathymetric Data
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An area within which a uniform assessment of the quality of the non-bathymetric data exists.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Data Coverage
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A geographical area that describes the coverage and extent of spatial objects.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Local Direction of Buoyage
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An area within which the navigational system of marks has been established in relation to a specific direction.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Navigational System of Marks
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An area within which the navigational system of marks has been established in relation to a specific direction.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Sounding Datum
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: The horizontal plane or tidal datum to which soundings have been reduced. Also called datum for sounding reduction.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Vertical Datum of Data
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: Any level surface (for example Mean Sea Level) taken as a surface of reference to which the elevations within a data set are reduced. Also called datum level, reference level, reference plane, levelling datum, datum for heights.
